    • Method Detail

      • findByAtt

        java.util.Collection<? extends MObject> findByAtt(MClass metaclass,
                                                  java.lang.String att,
                                                  java.lang.Object value)
        Get elements in the model from a metaclass, a meta attribute name and its value.

        If Element is given, every elements in the model will be checked.

        Parameters:
        metaclass - the metaclass to look for.
        att - the name of the meta attribute to check the value in.
        value - the value to look for in the attribute.
        Returns:
        A collection of elements matching the parameters. Might be empty but never null.

      • findByClass

        java.util.Collection<? extends MObject> findByClass(MClass metaclass)
        Get all elements in the model from their metaclass.
        Parameters:
        metaclass - the metaclass to look for.
        Returns:
        A list of all model elements, or null if no match is found.

      • getNoteType

        NoteType getNoteType(java.lang.String moduleName,
                     java.lang.String ownerName,
                     java.lang.String noteTypeName,
                     MClass metaclass)
              throws ElementNotUniqueException
        Find a note type by name and metaclass.
        Parameters:
        moduleName - the name of the module owing the note type, or a regular expression for module name matching. null or "" are interpreted as ".*", i.e. any module.
        ownerName - the name of the Stereotype or MetaclassReference owning the type. Cannot be null.
        noteTypeName - the note type name, or a regular expression. null or "" are interpreted as ".*", i.e. any note type.
        metaclass - a metaclass the note type must be applicable to.
        Returns:
        the found note type. Might be null is no element matches the given parameters.
        Throws:
        ElementNotUniqueException - when resolution is ambiguous and several note types match the given parameters
